gomodel:SYNGO_2783  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Nicotine effects on OFC neuroplasticity rely on NRG3/ErbB4 signaling\"\n- \"However, DL-AP5 did not block either nicotine- or NRG3-induced conversion of LTP to LTD (Figure 1b). These results indicate that acute application of either nicotine or NRG3 can strongly regulate the direction of long-term plasticity in the OFC and that this regulation is independent of NMDA receptor activation.\". Experimental description: - \"Male B6/129F1 and NRG3ska (Jackson Laboratories; 6-10 weeks of age; 20-25 g) were used in both the electrophysiology and molecular experiments. NRG3ska mice...\"\n- Applied NRG3 is of human species (traced back to supplier Sino Biological)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2783" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

